// LA-30 doc 5 §2 C4 (documented, not a change — ready-await never yields).
// Three promises are resolved BEFORE they are ever awaited, so every
// `await` below takes the fast/ready path (doc 1 §6): proceed without
// suspending, no scheduling point. Run with LANG_TASK_STATS=1: the
// `[tasks] switches=` count must equal the fixed per-process baseline for
// running task 0 alone (enter once, exit once — verified identical to a
// program with NO awaits at all), proving zero scheduler switches happened
// for this whole ready-chain. Byte-identical on oracle/IR/LLVM.
Promise<int> p1 = Promise();
p1.resolve(1);
Promise<int> p2 = Promise();
p2.resolve(2);
Promise<int> p3 = Promise();
p3.resolve(3);
int a = await p1;
int b = await p2;
int c = await p3;
console.writeln(a + b + c);
